In this article, President Trump is asked various questions by reporters on the South Lawn. He mentions that he has spoken to the family of someone, but it is unclear who. When asked about recent sharp remarks made by Chairman Xi of China and the Chinese foreign minister, Trump says it doesn't mean much. He is also questioned about Republicans' criticism of his budget, to which he responds by saying "Watch me." Finally, when asked about potential compromises with Republicans, Trump says he is ready to meet with them if they show him their budget.